In this article, President Barack Obama proclaims November as National Family Caregivers Month in the United States. The article recognizes the important role that family members, friends, and neighbors play in providing care to their loved ones. It acknowledges the sacrifices and dedication of family caregivers who often put their own lives on hold to support and care for their relatives. The article mentions various initiatives and programs, such as the National Family Caregiver Support Program and the Lifespan Respite Care Program, that aim to provide support and resources to caregivers. It also highlights the importance of workplace flexibility and the Caregivers and Veterans Omnibus Health Services Act in assisting caregivers. The article concludes by encouraging Americans to show appreciation and support for family caregivers and their loved ones.